reviews.review_text:
On the day that I was.. I can only imagine checking out the Grateful Dead            in this Brokedown Palace circa 72.
Watch out for that cut middle of El-Paso
Bird Song & Playin' light up a hefty 1st set.
Another time of transition for the band 
as Pigpen is out sick.
Greatest, Ramble on -very fiesty
especially DJG feelin' her way on dem G-SET vocals
Second set has a nice jam session
My highlight is Donna singing
on Across the Rio Grande
Phil pretty neat in that mix as well.
Jerry calling for the Sugar Magnolia
"She can make happy 
any man alive"
I had this in as a five but realistically 
with those cuts in Other1 & Sug Mag
it is probably a high 4
It is Weir doing the yelling during OMSN
